#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Veḷudvāravagga"
msgstr "1. At Bamboo Gate"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn55.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Veḷudvāreyyasutta"
msgstr "7. The People of Bamboo Gate"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena "
"saddhiṃ yena veḷudvāraṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together "
"with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the "
"Kosalan brahmins named Bamboo Gate."

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:"
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate heard:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.4"
msgid ""
"“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ "
"caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ veḷudvāraṃ anuppatto."
msgstr ""
"“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has "
"arrived at Bamboo Gate, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants."

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:"
msgstr "He has this good reputation:"

#. VAR: bhagavā → bhagavāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.7:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.7"
msgid ""
"So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ "
"sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti."
msgstr ""
"He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and "
"Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and "
"he makes it known to others."

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.8"
msgid ""
"So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ "
"sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good "
"in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice "
"that’s entirely full and pure."

msgctxt "sn55.7:1.9"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.353"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
"Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ "
"vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate went up to the Buddha. "
"Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and "
"polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some "
"announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. Seated to one side "
"they said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:2.2"
msgid "“mayaṃ, bho gotama, evaṅkāmā evaṃchandā evaṃadhippāyā—"
msgstr "“Master Gotama, these are our wishes, desires, and hopes."

msgctxt "sn55.7:2.3"
msgid ""
"puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvaseyyāma, kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhaveyyāma, "
"mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhāreyyāma, jātarūparajataṃ sādiyeyyāma, kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāma."
msgstr ""
"We wish to live at home with our children; to use sandalwood imported from "
"Kāsi; to wear garlands, perfumes, and makeup; and to accept gold and money. "
"And when our body breaks up, after death, we wish to be reborn in a good "
"place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn55.7:2.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no bhavaṃ gotamo amhākaṃ evaṅkāmānaṃ evaṃchandānaṃ evaṃadhippāyānaṃ "
"tathā dhammaṃ desetu yathā mayaṃ puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvaseyyāma … pe … "
"sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjeyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Given that we have such wishes, may the Buddha teach us the Dhamma so that "
"we may achieve them.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:3.1"
msgid "“Attupanāyikaṃ vo, gahapatayo, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Householders, I will teach you an explanation of the Dhamma that’s relevant "
"to oneself."

msgctxt "sn55.7:3.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn55.7:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho te veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn55.7:3.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.354"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:4.1"
msgid "“Katamo ca, gahapatayo, attupanāyiko dhammapariyāyo?"
msgstr "“And what is the explanation of the Dhamma that’s relevant to oneself?"

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.2"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.3"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khosmi jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo."
msgstr ""
"‘I want to live and don’t want to die; I want to be happy and recoil from "
"pain."

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho maṃ jīvitukāmaṃ amaritukāmaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhappaṭikūlaṃ jīvitā "
"voropeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Since this is so, if someone were to take my life, I wouldn’t like that."

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ jīvitukāmaṃ amaritukāmaṃ sukhakāmaṃ dukkhappaṭikūlaṃ "
"jīvitā voropeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But others also want to live and don’t want to die; they want to be happy "
"and recoil from pain. So if I were to take the life of someone else, they "
"wouldn’t like that either."

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.6"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo."
msgstr "The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others."

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.7"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on someone else?’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.8"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, parañca pāṇātipātā "
"veramaṇiyā samādapeti, pāṇātipātā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting in this way, they give up killing living creatures themselves. "
"And they encourage others to give up killing living creatures, praising the "
"giving up of killing living creatures."

msgctxt "sn55.7:4.9"
msgid "Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their bodily behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo kho me adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr "‘If someone were to steal from me, I wouldn’t like that."

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana parassa adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ "
"assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to steal from someone else, they wouldn’t like that either."

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo."
msgstr "The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others."

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on someone else?’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.6"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, parañca adinnādānā "
"veramaṇiyā samādapeti, adinnādānā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting in this way, they give up stealing themselves. And they encourage "
"others to give up stealing, praising the giving up of stealing."

msgctxt "sn55.7:5.7"
msgid "Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their bodily behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.2"
msgid "‘yo kho me dāresu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If someone were to have sexual relations with my wives, I wouldn’t like it."

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana parassa dāresu cārittaṃ āpajjeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa "
"appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to have sexual relations with someone else’s wives, he wouldn’"
"t like that either."

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo."
msgstr "The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by others."

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.5"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on others?’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.6"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, parañca "
"kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇiyā ca "
"vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting in this way, they give up sexual misconduct themselves. And they "
"encourage others to give up sexual misconduct, praising the giving up of "
"sexual misconduct."

msgctxt "sn55.7:6.7"
msgid "Evamassāyaṃ kāyasamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their bodily behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.355"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

# BB renders “damage my welfare with false speech”, which seems overly vague. The term attham bhanjati seems to only occur in this context, should it not have a meaning that applies to false speech? By analogy with the other passages, I take me as genitive here.
msgctxt "sn55.7:7.2"
msgid "‘yo kho me musāvādena atthaṃ bhañjeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr "‘If someone were to distort my meaning by lying, I wouldn’t like it."

msgctxt "sn55.7:7.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana parassa musāvādena atthaṃ bhañjeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa "
"appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to distort someone else’s meaning by lying, they wouldn’t like "
"it either."

msgctxt "sn55.7:7.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo."
msgstr "The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by someone else."

msgctxt "sn55.7:7.5"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on others?’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:7.6"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, parañca musāvādā "
"veramaṇiyā samādapeti, musāvādā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting in this way, they give up lying themselves. And they encourage "
"others to give up lying, praising the giving up of lying."

msgctxt "sn55.7:7.7"
msgid "Evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their verbal behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

#. VAR: vācāya mitte bhindeyya → mittehi bhedeyya (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn55.7:8.2"
msgid ""
"“yo kho maṃ pisuṇāya vācāya mitte bhindeyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If someone were to break me up from my friends by divisive speech, I wouldn’"
"t like it."

msgctxt "sn55.7:8.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ pisuṇāya vācāya mitte bhindeyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa "
"appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""
"But if I were to break someone else from their friends by divisive speech, "
"they wouldn’t like it either. …’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:8.4"
msgid "evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their verbal behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

# BB has “address’, but samudacarati usually has a negative sense of” beset, plague", etc.
msgctxt "sn55.7:9.2"
msgid ""
"“yo kho maṃ pharusāya vācāya samudācareyya, na metaṃ assa piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr "‘If someone were to attack me with harsh speech, I wouldn’t like it."

msgctxt "sn55.7:9.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ pharusāya vācāya samudācareyyaṃ, parassapi taṃ assa "
"appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to attack someone else with harsh speech, they wouldn’t like "
"it either. …’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:9.4"
msgid "Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.7:9.5"
msgid "evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their verbal behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple reflects:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo kho maṃ samphabhāsena samphappalāpabhāsena samudācareyya, na metaṃ assa "
"piyaṃ manāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If someone were to annoy me by talking silliness and nonsense, I wouldn’t "
"like it."

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañceva kho pana paraṃ samphabhāsena samphappalāpabhāsena samudācareyyaṃ, "
"parassapi taṃ assa appiyaṃ amanāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if I were to annoy someone else by talking silliness and nonsense, they "
"wouldn’t like it either.’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, parassa peso dhammo appiyo amanāpo."
msgstr "The thing that is disliked by me is also disliked by another."

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.5"
msgid ""
"Yo kho myāyaṃ dhammo appiyo amanāpo, kathāhaṃ paraṃ tena saṃyojeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Since I dislike this thing, how can I inflict it on another?’"

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.6"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya attanā ca samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, parañca "
"samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā samādapeti, samphappalāpā veramaṇiyā ca vaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting in this way, they give up talking nonsense themselves. And they "
"encourage others to give up talking nonsense, praising the giving up of "
"talking nonsense."

msgctxt "sn55.7:10.7"
msgid "Evamassāyaṃ vacīsamācāro tikoṭiparisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So their verbal behavior is purified in three points."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.356"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:11.1"
msgid "So buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "And they have experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.7:11.2"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.7:11.3"
msgid "dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.7:11.4"
msgid ""
"saṃghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṃgho …"
" pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti."
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

msgctxt "sn55.7:11.5"
msgid ""
"ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to "
"immersion."

#. VAR: saddhammehi → dhammehi (bj)
msgctxt "sn55.7:11.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, gahapatayo, ariyasāvako imehi sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti "
"imehi catūhi ākaṅkhiyehi ṭhānehi, so ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple has these seven good qualities and these four "
"desirable states they may, if they wish, declare of themselves:"

#. VAR: khīṇatiracchānayoni → khīṇatiracchānayoniyo (bj, s1-3, km) | khīṇatiracchānayoniko (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn55.7:11.7"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. "
"I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a "
"stream-enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound "
"for awakening.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.7:12.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, veḷudvāreyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Bamboo Gate said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn55.7:12.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! …"

msgctxt "sn55.7:12.3"
msgid ""
"ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

#. VAR: pāṇupete → pānupete (pts1) | pāṇupetaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn55.7:12.4"
msgid "Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.7:12.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
